If I could give zero stars I would. A group from my school came to this Subway yesterday around 45 minutes before closing. The man working there, named Lionel, flatly refused to take our orders, complaining that it would be "too much" and he "couldn't do it." We left the restaurant and decided to go to Sonic instead. 3 of us stayed, thinking that he could hopefully handle that. While making our food he was rude and uncooperative. He was sarcastic, asking if a friend of mine wanted lettuce in her salad. He refused to give my friend her cookie, because he put the order in incorrectly, and blamed it on "inventory." Additionally, the food smelled off and the vegetables were limp. All in all, I usually love Subway, but this specific employee has really put a damper on that. Suffice it to say that his manager has been notified. There are many Subway's near here with much better quality and service, that I would recommend much, much more.
